1)    You are given a string s. The score of a string is defined as the sum of the absolute difference between the ASCII values of adjacent characters.
Return the score of s.
Example 1:
Input: s = "code"
Output: 24

class Solution {
    public int scoreOfString(String s) {
        char[] arr=s.toCharArray();
        int sum=0;
        
        for(int i=0;i<arr.length-1;i++){
              int sub=arr[i]-arr[i+1];
              if(sub<0){
                sub=-(sub);
              }
              sum+=sub;
        }
        return sum;
    }
}

ALTERNATE SOLUTION

class Solution {
public int scoreOfString(String s) {
int count= 0;
for(int i = 1;i<s.length();i++){
count+=Math.abs(s.charAt(i)-s.charAt(i-1));
}
return count;
}
}
